-- Morgan Stanley's Brazil Economist Carvalho Leaves After Three-Year Stint
-- Tal Barak Harif
-- 2010-07-01T22:05:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/morgan-stanley-s-brazil-economist-carvalho-leaves-after-three-year-stint.html

          
          
             Marcelo Carvalho, the chief Brazil
economist at Morgan Stanley, has left after a three-year stint
with the firm in Sao Paulo.  
 Sandra Hernandez, a spokeswoman with Morgan Stanley in New
York, declined to say why Carvalho left. Carvalho joined Morgan
Stanley in June 2007 from the International Monetary Fund. He
has also covered the Brazilian economy at ING Bank NV, Banco
Itau SA and JPMorgan Chase & Co.  
